Title: Complete Cat Food
Description: Always choose a ‘complete’ cat food, one that contains all the nutrition they need in one single food source. This will ensure they’re getting all the vital nutrients.

Title: Dry Cat Food
Description: Cats are very particular about what they like and what they don’t. Dry food contains less water, so your cat may drink more.

Title: Wet Cat Food
Description: Wet and dry cat food have very different textures and smells, so offer them both and see which they prefer.

Title: Kitten Food
Description: Make sure to pick a food specifically for kittens, as they have different needs compared to adult cats.

Title: Commercially Available Raw Cat Food
Description: Opt for these over homemade raw diets to ensure balanced nutrition and safety.

Title: Cat Treats
Description: It's fine to give occasional treats, but be wary of overfeeding.

Title: Human Food (Occasional Treats)
Description: Small amounts of well-cooked fresh fish or chicken are safe as an occasional treat.

Title: Vegetarian Diet
Description: Not recommended, as cats are obligate carnivores and need meat to stay healthy.

Title: Vegan Diet
Description: Not advisable for the same reasons as vegetarian; cats require nutrients found only in animal products.

Title: Puzzle Feeder
Description: To make food time more exciting, consider putting a portion of dry food into a puzzle feeder.
